title: Key Verbal Behaviours
body:
What is said and how it is said are two key factors that can help you detect deception.  

Let’s look at what these factors consist of and then find out how changes in any one of them may be a indicator of deception. 

Select the items to see the characteristics associated with each. 

Later you will be provided examples and asked to identify the type of response.
